In his inaugural address, President Joe Biden called for unity and healing in the United States. He acknowledged the challenges facing the country, including the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, racial injustice, political extremism, and climate change. He emphasized the importance of democracy and the need to defend the truth against lies. Biden pledged to be a President for all Americans, regardless of political affiliation, and urged the nation to come together to overcome its current crises. He expressed hope for a brighter future and called on the American people to join him in working towards a more prosperous and united country.